line_1: The many weary miles I've travelled,
line_2: (For, by my truth, but ill my days I've sped)

line_1: The many weary miles I've travelled,
line_2: Your hair would stand upright upon your head.

line_1: The many weary miles I've travelled,
line_2: By me to Columbella must be led:

line_1: TO EGYPT from CHALDEE it travell'd,
line_2: And Fate at MEMPHIS was unravell'd,
